        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 8:10PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 810 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of San Jon, or 15 miles southeast of Tucumcari, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Jon and Bard.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 348 and 362.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
